Behavioural issues have been reported as challenging and timely recognition and initiation of treatment may be helpful. Notably, reports are emerging of new incident cases of psychosis - seemingly in an older group of people - associated with exposure to the psychosocial stress of COVID-19 (
 Hu et al., 2020; 
 Zulkifli et al., 2020). While extreme caution should be applied in inferring an association given the limited amount of available data, increased awareness and vigilance may be justified.
